delta_rule_sm120_sm121a.patch — GB10 (sm_121a) arch retarget for the AOT export.

Recreates the local gx10 edit the shipped libatlasgdn.so was built with (the
.so's embedded compile line is "-arch sm_121a"; the .bak_sm121 noted in
gdn_export_f32.py was reverted). ONE line: the explicit GPUArch compile option.
custom_compile_cache.py needs NO change: with "sm_121a" the option no longer
matches _needs_sm120a_tma_patch, so the sm_120a PTX TMA rewrite + forced
CU_TARGET_COMPUTE_120A JIT loader are bypassed — the June-30 export ran the
kernel bit-exactly on gx10 through exactly this clean path.

Apply order (from /home/ms/flashinfer, pristine checkout):
  1. patch flashinfer/gdn_kernels/delta_rule_dsl/delta_rule_sm120.py \
       < delta_rule_sm120_aot_export.patch
  2. patch -p1 < delta_rule_sm120_sm121a.patch     (this file)
  3. patch -p1 < delta_rule_sm120_f32_out.patch    (variant A + B)
  4. patch -p1 < delta_rule_sm120_f32_inverse.patch (variant B only)

--- a/flashinfer/gdn_kernels/delta_rule_dsl/delta_rule_sm120.py
+++ b/flashinfer/gdn_kernels/delta_rule_dsl/delta_rule_sm120.py
